<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Strategy Blog — Free Tips & Word Lists" description="Scrabble strategy articles: tile values, rack management, dictionaries, and competitive play. Level up your game with our free instant word finder." keywords="scrabble blog, scrabble strategy tips, two letter scrabble words, scrabble tile values, free scrabble word finder, scrabble bingo words, rare words, dictionary, puzzle, word games, tile rack, high scoring word">

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What topics does the Scrabble blog cover?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The blog covers strategy guides, word lists (two-letter, three-letter, bingos), high-scoring tips, tournament preparation, dictionaries (SOWPODS vs TWL), and Scrabble history and culture." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is the Scrabble word finder free to use?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, ScrabbleWordsFinder.com is completely free with no sign-up required. It includes a real-time solver, tile probability tracker, rack leave analysis, and best opening moves — all updating as you type." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many articles are on the Scrabble blog?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The blog has over 950 articles covering beginner guides, advanced strategy, word lists by letter, scoring techniques, and competitive Scrabble tips — with new content added regularly." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-4 pb-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-2">
      <span class="text-blue-400">Scrabble</span> Blog
    </h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4"><a href="/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">ScrabbleWordsFinder.com</a> is a free, instant <a href="/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">word solver</a> that works as you type — no sign-up, no waiting. Enter up to 15 tiles (including blanks with ?) and get every valid word ranked by score, sorted by length, or filtered by starting/ending letters. The solver supports both <a href="/blog/twl-vs-sowpods/" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">SOWPODS and TWL dictionaries</a> with 335,000+ words from 2 to 15 letters.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Beyond word finding, you get live <a href="/#section-probability" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">tile probability</a> showing what's left in the bag, automatic <a href="/#section-rack-leave" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">rack leave analysis</a> scoring your remaining tiles, and <a href="/#section-best-opening" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">best opening moves</a> with double-word scoring calculated in real time. Save words to your collection with one-click dictionary definitions, track your progress with achievements, and export your word list anytime.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Reference panels give you instant access to all <a href="/#section-two-letter" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">two-letter words</a>, top <a href="/#section-three-letter" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">three-letter words</a>, <a href="/#section-q-no-u" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">Q-without-U words</a>, and <a href="/#section-rare-letters" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">rare high-scoring letter combinations</a>. Everything updates automatically as you play — no buttons to click for secondary information. <a href="/guide/" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">📘 Read the full guide →</a></p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">This blog covers <a href="/blog/strategy/" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">strategy</a>, <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">word lists</a>, <a href="/blog/high-scoring/" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">scoring tips</a>, and <a href="/blog/scrabble-history-origins-great-depression/" class="text-purple-400 underline decoration-purple-500/50 decoration-1 underline-offset-2 hover:text-purple-300">game history</a> to help you dominate the board. <span id="article-count" class="text-gray-500"></span></p>

